{"id":67160,"global_id":"www.smilefoundationindia.org?id=67160","global_id_lineage":["www.smilefoundationindia.org?id=67160"],"author":"2","status":"publish","date":"2019-10-03 20:36:43","date_utc":"2019-10-03 15:06:43","modified":"2023-05-31 11:14:02","modified_utc":"2023-05-31 05:44:02","url":"https:\/\/www.smilefoundationindia.org\/workshops-events\/child-friendly-city-initiative-held-in-chandigarh\/","rest_url":"https:\/\/www.smilefoundationindia.org\/wp-json\/tribe\/events\/v1\/events\/67160","title":"Child Friendly city initiative held in Chandigarh","description":"<p>A child friendly city initiative was held in Chandigarh on the 3rd of October 2019. The initiative seeks to draw attention on children&#8217;s rights, namely; Right to Education, Right to Participation, Right to health, Right to play and leisure &amp; Right to safety.<\/p>\n<p>Under the Child for Child programme, Smile Foundation visits various schools and conducts engaging sessions for the young minds and also teachers and partents. It sensitizes children towards various causes and let them realize their privileged status and conducts health checkups regularly.<\/p>\n<p>CFC currently reaches out to nearly one million privileged children in 900 schools spread across 417 districts of India, every year. In addition, their parents and teachers are also involved in the process. The programme has today reached out to each part of India with the exception of Lakshadweep.<\/p>\n<p>Smile Foundation is an NGO in India directly benefitting over 600,000 children and their families every year, through more than 250 live welfare projects on education, healthcare, livelihood and women empowerment, in over 950 remote villages and slums across 25 states of India.<\/p>","excerpt":"","slug":"child-friendly-city-initiative-held-in-chandigarh","image":{"url":"https:\/\/www.smilefoundationindia.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/child-friendly-cfc-3oct19.jpg","id":67161,"extension":"jpg","width":1926,"height":600,"f